name: NewSubfileType
desc: A general indication of the kind of data contained in this subfile.

name: SubfileType
desc: A general indication of the kind of data contained in this subfile.

name: ImageWidth
desc: The number of columns in the image, i.e., the number of pixels per row.

name: ImageLength
desc: The number of rows of pixels in the image.

name: BitsPerSample
desc: Number of bits per component.

name: Compression
desc: Compression scheme used on the image data.

name: PhotometricInterpretation
desc: The color space of the image data.

name: Threshholding
desc: For black and white TIFF files that represent shades of gray, the technique used to convert from gray to black and white pixels.

name: CellWidth
desc: The width of the dithering or halftoning matrix used to create a dithered or halftoned bilevel file.

name: CellLength
desc: The length of the dithering or halftoning matrix used to create a dithered or halftoned bilevel file.

name: FillOrder
desc: The logical order of bits within a byte.

name: ImageDescription
desc: A string that describes the subject of the image.

name: Make
desc: The scanner manufacturer.

name: Model
desc: The scanner model name or number.

name: StripOffsets
desc: For each strip, the byte offset of that strip.

name: Orientation
desc: The orientation of the image with respect to the rows and columns.

name: SamplesPerPixel
desc: The number of components per pixel.

name: RowsPerStrip
desc: The number of rows per strip.

name: StripByteCounts
desc: For each strip, the number of bytes in the strip after compression.

name: MinSampleValue
desc: The minimum component value used.

name: MaxSampleValue
desc: The maximum component value used.

name: XResolution
desc: The number of pixels per ResolutionUnit in the ImageWidth direction.

name: YResolution
desc: The number of pixels per ResolutionUnit in the ImageLength direction.

name: PlanarConfiguration
desc: How the components of each pixel are stored.

name: FreeOffsets
desc: For each string of contiguous unused bytes in a TIFF file, the byte offset of the string.

name: FreeByteCounts
desc: For each string of contiguous unused bytes in a TIFF file, the number of bytes in the string.

name: GrayResponseUnit
desc: The precision of the information contained in the GrayResponseCurve.

name: GrayResponseCurve
desc: For grayscale data, the optical density of each possible pixel value.

name: ResolutionUnit
desc: The unit of measurement for XResolution and YResolution.

name: Software
desc: Name and version number of the software package(s) used to create the image.

name: DateTime
desc: Date and time of image creation.

name: Artist
desc: Person who created the image.

name: HostComputer
desc: The computer and/or operating system in use at the time of image creation.

name: ColorMap
desc: A color map for palette color images.

name: ExtraSamples
desc: Description of extra components.

name: Copyright
desc: Copyright notice.
